The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE SOIREE

 (Kala Mandir, 6 pm, November 12) Santoor exponent Pandit 

 Shiv Kumar Sharma and vocalist Pandit Ajoy Chakraborty will 

 take the stage to play some soulful raga-based tracks 

 from Hindi films. Organised by Sangeet Kala Mandir. 

 THE BOOK

 (The Cyrstal Hall, Taj Bengal, 7.30 pm, November 13) The 

 Last Mughal: The Fall of a Dynasty, Delhi, 1857, by 

 William Dalrymple will be launched. It is a Penguin publication.

 THE FEST

 (Rabindra Sadan, till November 17) Roberto Rossellinis 

 Stromboli will be screened at 9.15 am on November 

 15. Also in line are Ingmar Bergmans Through 

 a Glass Darkly (Nov 13, 11.15), Winter Light (Nov 

 14, 9.15 am) and The Silence (Nov 17, 11.15 am). 

 Robert Wises West Side Story is slated for Nov 16 

 at 11.15 am. 

 THE TV SHOW

 (Animal 

 Planet, 9 pm, November 12) When bamboo flowers, famine death 

 and destruction will soon follow, or so goes the tribal saying 

 in the Northeast. The one-hour special looks at this cycle 

 of famine and plague that recurs every 48 years. Animal Planet 

 visits the villagers preparing for a catastrophe as the bamboo 

 starts flowering again in 2006. They hope the jinx will be 

 broken this time. 




